            h2 Festival Booths
            p
                | Each year, the Festival of Nations hosts hundreds of booths in the various festival areas, including
                | the International Café*, the Global Marketplace & Bazaar*, our Cultural Exhibits, and
                | Ethnic Demonstrations.
            p
                | The Festival of Nations celebrates the many cultures of the world that are represented here in
                | Minnesota. Festival of Nations participants must meet certain criteria in order to be part of the
                | Festival, including the following:
            ul
                li Booth workers must be dressed in traditional ethnic clothing
                li
                    | All merchandise or food being sold in a booth must represent the ethnicity being presented
                li
                    | Examples of mass-produced items that are prohibited include Barbie dolls in traditional
                    | costumes, T-shirts of any kind, and knives, swords and other potentially dangerous toys
                li Participant is in good standing with the International Institute of Minnesota
                li Applications will be considered in order received
            p
                | If you are interested in participating at the Festival of Nations by hosting an International Café,
                | a Marketplace & Bazaar booth, a Cultural Exhibit and/or an Ethnic Demonstration, please complete
